Hey everyone, what is the best way to compare two dates in HubSpot?
I am making  an  event list for a client. I want to compare:

`if current date &gt;= event date`  then show the event.

I'm not sure what  the best datetimeformat to evaluate this expression.

```    {% set todayDate = local_dt|datetimeformat('%Y %m %d') %}
    {% set eventEndDate = row.end_date|datetimeformat('%Y %m %d') %}
    {% if todayDate &gt;= eventEndDate %}
		show only live events
	{% endif %}```
